Everything here still functions the same as it did before, for the most part. There are a couple of discrepancies that I'm aware of, which I'll point out when I get to them. (You might've already noticed one of them, but I'll mention it later.)
M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M
AWESOME!!! Hey, let's use the left+right glitch to collect them faster!

MOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOONNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS!!!!!!!!!!!!!

And, of course, I've gotta go for the moon! Be sure not to leave too many things alive up here (no more than two sprites), or else some of the eating blocks in the room below might fail to spawn. And, if the eating block for the letter "O" doesn't spawn, then you can't get the moon! (Unless you brought the P-switch for some reason.)
There we go! Alright, time for more moons!
There's still a Fire Flower in this note block, and there's still a star in the other note block, which I will be getting.

Okay, back outside, I can go back for the P-switch.
Whoops, I missed. Anyway, here's what the third underground area looks like.

You're welcome!

So, what's the second underground area look like?

Okay, let's try this again, without accidentally destroying the shell I need.

Ah, that's better. Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through this graphically-modified version of my Eating Block Ruins level! And, thanks go to Roadhog360 for modifying the graphics! See y'all later!

Okay, here's the first discrepancy I'm aware of. Midpoint here was lowered closer to the ground, and half of the platform representing the arch ledge that was here is missing. I'm guessing the original setup didn't work well with Roadhog360's GFX here or something.
Oh, I'm unlocking something here.
...Maybe...
